We started with a function
that we knew was continuous.

00:03:44.410 --> 00:03:47.760
We knew the integral from
0 to x of that function

00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:50.610
was equal to a
certain function of x.

00:03:50.610 --> 00:03:53.447
And we wanted to evaluate
this function at a certain,

00:03:53.447 --> 00:03:55.430
at a certain point.

00:03:55.430 --> 00:03:57.430
So what we exploited was
the fundamental theorem

00:03:57.430 --> 00:03:58.986
of calculus.

00:03:58.986 --> 00:04:00.610
And the fundamental
theorem of calculus

00:04:00.610 --> 00:04:06.010
